# From one-liners to production

The capstone. Modules 01–09 taught the *pieces*; this ties them into the two skills that make a sysadmin.

```
     write it once         ·          fix it fast
 ┌────────────────────┐        ┌────────────────────────┐
 │  shell scripting    │        │  troubleshooting        │
 │ vars · if · for     │        │  disk · mem · CPU       │
 │ functions · set -e  │        │  network · services     │
 └────────────────────┘        └────────────────────────┘
  lx-shell / lx-streams          every subsystem you've met
```

## Two halves

- **Scripting** — shebang, args, conditionals, loops, functions, `set -euo pipefail`
- **Troubleshooting** — a methodology + **five playbooks**: full disk, OOM, runaway CPU, dead network, dead service

## Then the professional layer

**MAC** (SELinux/AppArmor) · **performance** (`vmstat`/`iostat`) · the **LFCS exam** — what to expect and how to pass.
